<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="387" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,261,1512]" pageId="5" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1450,1476]" pageId="5" pageNumber="387">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[932,986,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="387">medi</emphasis>
- and the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1159,1252,1450,1475]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="387">spinatus</emphasis>
, referring to the clustered short spines at the middle of the valva ventrally in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
